    <name>Geronimo :: Messaging</name>
    <groupId>geronimo-sandbox</groupId>
    <id>geronimo-sandbox-messaging</id>
    <shortDescription>Geronimo Messaging</shortDescription>
    <description>Geronimo Messaging provides a message passing framework
    for inter-node communications. Messages, abstracted by the Msg object,
    are exchanged between peers, abstracted by the EndPoint object. These
    peers/EndPoints are mounted by peer servers, abstracted by the Node object,
    in charge of providing the transport layer service. Peer servers or Nodes
    have the ability to join or leave other Nodes.
    Geronimo Messaging provides also a primitive remote invocation layer on
    top of this message passing framework along with a primitive reference
    layer. These primitive implementations allow services mounted by Nodes
    to be referenced/invoked from remote Nodes.
    </description>
    <url>http://incubator.apache.org/projects/geronimo/messaging/</url>
    <siteDirectory>/www/incubator.apache.org/projects/geronimo/messaging</siteDirectory>
    <distributionDirectory>/www/incubator.apache.org/projects/geronimo/builds/messaging</distributionDirectory>

